{
  "name": "SOX Compliance Evidence Collector",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## SOX Compliance Evidence Collector\n\n### What this workflow does\n1. Watches a Google Drive folder for SOX evidence documents\n2. Downloads the evidence file\n3. PDF Vector extracts control evidence fields\n4. PDF Vector Ask reviews whether the evidence supports the control\n5. Merges extraction and assessment\n6. Formats the audit record\n7. Logs evidence to Google Sheets\n8. Sends Slack alerts for deficiencies or remediation needs\n\n### Setup steps\n1. Create a Google Drive folder for incoming SOX evidence\n2. Create a Google Sheet with columns for Control ID, Control Name, Owner, Process Area, Test Result, Deficiency Type, Remediation Required, Due Date, File Name, and Processed Date\n3. Add PDF Vector credentials\n4. Add Slack channel for compliance alerts\n5. Update folder, sheet, and channel IDs\n\n### Use case\nFinance, compliance, and audit teams collecting control evidence for SOX testing.\n\n### Template by PDF Vector\npdfvector.com/integrations/n8n",
        "height": 700,
        "width": 460,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "6f2d5ac4-3848-4a32-b6a8-4b706510c940",
      "name": "Sticky Note",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        540,
        220
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "pollTimes": {
          "item": [
            {
              "mode": "everyMinute"
            }
          ]
        },
        "triggerOn": "specificFolder",
        "folderToWatch": {
          "__rl": true,
          "value": "YOUR_SOX_EVIDENCE_FOLDER_ID",
          "mode": "id",
          "cachedResultName": "SOX Evidence Intake"
        },
        "event": "fileCreated",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "4b8a60f1-2d91-42d7-b0b2-1f369f812d30",
      "name": "New Evidence Document",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.googleDriveTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1060,
        420
      ],
      "credentials": {
        "googleDriveOAuth2Api": {
          "id": "YOUR_GOOGLE_DRIVE_CREDENTIAL_ID",
          "name": "Google Drive account"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "download",
        "fileId": {
